Note: For each variable used in the final models, the end use(s) it appears in and how it is used there are indicated as follows. For the components, "SPH" refers to space heating, "WTH" refers to water heating, "COL" refers to air conditioning, "RFG" refers to refrigerators, and "OTH" refers to all other purposes. For the mathematical form, a variable is either "B", part of a base term , or "A", part of an adjustment term. For example, AIRCOND has a value of "COL_B" in the Electricity column, which means AIRCOND is included in a base term for the air conditioning component of the electricity end-use model. For further information about the end-use models, please see "End Use Model FAQs", posted on the RECS methodology page.
